sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Envoy as Envoy Gateway<br/>80/443 TCP
    participant EPP as EPP (ext-proc)<br/>9002/TCP gRPC
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant vLLM as vLLM Pod (selected)<br/>8000/TCP HTTP

    Note over Client,vLLM: Flow 1: Standard Inference Request Routing

    Client->>Envoy: POST /v1/completions<br/>HTTP/HTTPS (TLS if configured)<br/>Auth: Model API key
    Envoy->>EPP: ext-proc ProcessingRequest<br/>gRPC plaintext<br/>Request headers + body metadata
    EPP->>K8sAPI: Watch InferencePool, InferenceModel,<br/>Pods, EndpointSlices<br/>HTTPS/TLS, SA token
    Note over EPP: Run scheduling pipeline:<br/>1. Filters (by-label, decode/prefill)<br/>2. Scorers (prefix-cache, load-aware, session-affinity)<br/>3. Select optimal pod
    EPP-->>Envoy: ProcessingResponse<br/>gRPC plaintext<br/>Target: pod-ip:8000
    Envoy->>vLLM: Forward inference request<br/>HTTP plaintext, port 8000
    vLLM-->>Envoy: Inference response<br/>HTTP plaintext
    Envoy-->>Client: JSON response<br/>HTTP/HTTPS

    Note over Client,vLLM: Flow 2: Disaggregated Prefill/Decode (P/D)

    participant PrefillPod as Prefill vLLM Pod<br/>8000/TCP HTTP
    participant DecodePod as Decode vLLM Pod<br/>8000/TCP HTTP

    Client->>Envoy: POST /v1/completions<br/>HTTP/HTTPS
    Envoy->>EPP: ext-proc ProcessingRequest<br/>gRPC plaintext
    Note over EPP: PdProfileHandler evaluates:<br/>1. Run decode profile first<br/>2. Check prompt length vs threshold<br/>3. Check prefix cache hit rate<br/>4. If suffix > threshold → run prefill profile
    EPP-->>Envoy: ProcessingResponse<br/>Target: decode-pod-ip:8000<br/>Header: x-prefiller-host-port=prefill-pod:8000
    Envoy->>DecodePod: Forward with prefill header<br/>HTTP plaintext
    DecodePod->>PrefillPod: Remote prefill request<br/>HTTP plaintext, port 8000
    PrefillPod-->>DecodePod: Prefill result (KV-cache blocks)
    Note over DecodePod: Run local decode<br/>using prefilled KV-cache
    DecodePod-->>Envoy: Streaming response<br/>HTTP plaintext
    Envoy-->>Client: Streaming JSON response

    Note over Client,vLLM: Flow 3: KV-Cache Event Tracking (cache_tracking mode)

    participant vLLMZMQ as vLLM Pod<br/>5557/TCP ZMQ
    participant KVIndexer as KV-Cache Indexer<br/>(in-process)

    vLLMZMQ->>EPP: ZMQ PUB/SUB<br/>KV-cache block events<br/>plaintext, port 5557
    Note over EPP: ZMQ SUB socket receives<br/>KV-cache block add/remove events
    EPP->>KVIndexer: Feed events to indexer<br/>(in-process)
    Note over KVIndexer: Update prefix-cache index<br/>Track which blocks cached on which pods
    KVIndexer->>EPP: Cache scores for<br/>prefix-cache-scorer<br/>(in-process)
